('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SEED_ROUND','kapiva',NULL,'Kapiva is a brand of Ayurvedic herbal supplements and meal replacement products. Product catalog includes ayurvedic teas, nutrition powders, honey, medical & health products, and more. The company also operates offline wellness clinics. The company is a sister concern of the Baidyanath Group.''','http://kapiva.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','UNFUNDED','adda',NULL,'Adda is a residential complex management solutions provider. The solution portfolio includes Adda ERP and Adda Gatekeeper solution. Features of the Adda application include visitor notification, property maintenance, expected visitor, bill payments, community portals and emergency help.''','http://adda.io')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','DE Shaw',NULL,NULL,'http://www.deshawindia.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','MediaTek',NULL,'MediaTek is a Taiwan based fabless semiconductor company for wireless communications and digital multimedia solutions. The company is a System on Chips (SOC) solutions provider for wireless communications, high-definition TV, optical storage, DVD and Blu-ray products. Mediatek stood 10th among semiconductor vendors globally in terms of revenue generated improving its rank by 5 places. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $7.9B, and a net profit of $688M.''','http://mediatek.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNKNOWN','SAS',NULL,'SAS provides business analytics software, enterprise data management software and services, and is the largest independent vendor in the business intelligence market for end to end BI solution. It also enables creation of seamless access to the Pig and Hive languages and the MapReduce framework to explore and visualize data stored in Hadoop to discover patterns and publish reports. Provides business views delivered through dashboards, visualizations, e-mail alerts, mobile applications, self-service, and visual data exploration tools. Gartner positioned SAS as a Leader in the Magic Quadrant for BI and Analytics Platforms in 2015''','http://www.sas.com/en_us/home.html')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','IPO','Google',NULL,'Google provides search and advertising services, which together aim to organize and monetize the world‚Äôs information. In addition to its dominant search engine, it offers a plethora of online tools and platforms including Gmail, Maps, YouTube, and Google+, the company‚Äôs extension into the social space. Most of its Web-based products are free, funded by Google‚Äôs highly integrated online advertising platforms AdWords and AdSense. Google has also made strong moves into the web-based apps space with acquisitions of JotSpot (documents), 2Web Technologies (spreadsheets) and Zenter (presentations). The company has also acquired YouTube, DoubleClick, and Feedburner.''','https://google.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','SAP Labs',NULL,'SAP is the world leader in enterprise software products and services. It caters to companies of all sizes. Based on market capitalization, it is the third-largest independent software manufacturer. SAP ERP, its ERP offering streamlines procurement, manufacturing, sales, finance, accounting and HR of a company. Could be purchased as on-premise software or hosted on the cloud. SAP HANA Cloud Platform is an open platform-as-a-service providing in-memory database and business application services. Hana Cloud Integrators integrate with CRM, ECC, and ERP on-premise as wells as SAP CRM. Solutions for enterprise information management (EIM) support abilities to architect, integrate, improve, manage, associate, and archive information. Provides SAP S/4HANA Cloud, SAP Product Lifecycle Management, SAP Digital Manufacturing, and SAP Asset Intelligence Network which are used to build digital twins. Its major clients are Step Up for Students, Auras, Cascades, and Excellerate. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $29.1B, and a net profit of $4.8B''','http://www.sap.com/index.html')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Samsung',NULL,'Samsung is a multinational conglomerate company with many subsidiaries including Samsung Electronics, Samsung Heavy Industries, Samsung Engineering, Samsung CT, Samsung Life Insurance, Samsung Everland & Cheil Worldwide. For the consumer market, Samsung electronics develops, manufactures and sells various products including mobile devices, cameras, home appliances, wearable technology, audio/video, memory storage, etc. Samsung sells these consumer products through various channels including their online store, various offline and online retailers across geographies. Lee Byung-Chul is Samsung''s founder & Jong Kyun-Shin is the CEO. In 2018, the company recorded revenues of $221.5B, and a net profit of $39.9B''','http://www.samsung.com/us/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_B','tonbo imaging pvt.ltd',NULL,'Tonbo Imaging designs, builds and deploys advanced imaging and sensor systems for military reconnaissance and security of critical government and industrial establishments. It''s systems allow soldiers to see during day and night, through fog and foliage, and do real-time interpretation of battlefield environment. Its applications also include surveillance - sensing automobile collisions before they happen. The company has 15 patents awaiting approval and offices in Singapore and Palo Alto, US as well. Bagged a $100 million contract to manufacture and export ‚Äònight-vision sights‚Äô for guns to be sold by a US company to the Peruvian army.''','http://tonboimaging.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_DPLUS','PayMate',NULL,'PayMate allows businesses to automate and manage vendor payments (AP), customer payments (AR), invoicing, and cash flow. Offers NEFT, RTGS, IMPS, Cards, and Netbanking payment options. Users can also view, analyze, and manage business using its cloud-based platform. Businesses can also apply for working capital loans through the platform.''','http://paymate.in/')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Nutanix',NULL,'Nutanix offers compute and storage infrastructure for implementing enterprise-class virtualization without complex and expensive network storage (SAN or NAS). Built on architectural techniques employed in core infrastructure systems at Google, Nutanix Complete Cluster‚Äôs converged compute and storage architecture can scale to manage petabytes of data while running thousands of virtual machines. Since emerging from stealth mode in April 2011, Nutanix has raised $172 million in four funding rounds from top tier VCs that include Kholsa Ventures, Lightspeed Venture Partners, Goldman Sachs, Battery Ventures and Blumberg Capital. Nutanix has been named to Gigaom‚Äôs Top 50 Cloud Innovators list and won 2011 Best of VMworld Gold award''','http://www.nutanix.com/en')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','HEALTHTECH','SEED_ROUND','wellthy therapeutics',NULL,'Wellthy Therapeutics is a provider of an app for managing diabetes. It allows users to calculate their diabetic health and glucose level in blood. It provides a lifestyle management program for people with chronic diseases like chronic kidney disease (CKD) and other such chronic conditions and offers solutions like lifestyle tracker, interactive lessons, expert coaching, personalized feedback, emergency alert, and assistance, experienced diabetes educator support, detailed lifestyle reports, and many more. It also offers the provider dashboard to keep track of their patient''s progress.''','http://wellthy.care')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','TRAVELTECH','SERIES_DPLUS','OYO Rooms',NULL,'OYO Rooms is an online marketplace for branded budget accommodation with a standardized stay experience. The company operates on an asset-light model by aggregating & managing hotel rooms from partners. The app enables users to search and book hotel rooms after providing relevant details. Its mobile app is available for iOS and Android devices. Also offers Oyo Cafe, an aggregator of partner hotels'' kitchens and Oyo Care, an on-demand room servicing facility for its partners. In March 2016, the company partnered with PayPal to enable global transactions. In 2018, the company also launched Oyo Living, a managed long-term rental service in select locations.''','http://www.oyorooms.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','MEDIA_AND_ENTERTAINMENT','SERIES_A','vokal',NULL,'Vokal is a Bengaluru-based peer-to-peer knowledge and opinion-sharing platform for non-English Internet users. Users can ask questions using the voice/text option and knowledge contributors can respond in either mode to the same. The contents cover the areas of entertainment, news, information, and knowledge. The platform has a live video-streaming feature, where experts share their knowledge with users. Claims to have more than 300K questions on its platform and over 1,000 questions are asked every day on different topics, to date. As of January 2019, it is available in Hindi and plans to launch in multiple languages such as Tamil, Telugu, Marathi, Kannada, Gujarati, Malayalam, Punjabi, and Oriya.''','http://getvokal.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SEED_ROUND','InterviewBit',NULL,'InterviewBit is an online platform for tech interview preparation. The platform offers gamified lessons with video tutorials, primer problems and guided solutions for programming, scripting, databases, system design, puzzles, etc. The platform also enables the candidates to get connected with the right companies worldwide based on skills and preferences.''','http://www.interviewbit.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','FINTECH','SERIES_A','smallcase',NULL,'Smallcase is an online platform which provides users a professionally built basket of stocks called "smallcases". This basket can contain up to 20 stocks which can be based on market trends, announcements, events, etc. Users have to pay a flat fee of INR 100 to buy a smallcase. As of July 2016, the company is in beta stage and is accepting new registrations from clients of its brokerage partner, Zerodha.''','http://smallcase.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Accenture',NULL,'Accenture is a global management consulting, technology services and outsourcing company, with approximately 204,000 people serving clients in more than 120 countries. Its services include Accenture Strategy provides business strategy, technology strategy, and operations strategy services. Accenture Consulting provides technology, business and management consulting. Accenture Digital provides digital marketing, analytics, and mobility services. Accenture Technology focuses on technology solutions, implementation, delivery, and research & development, including its Technology Labs for emerging technologies. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $42.5B, and a net profit of $4.5B''','http://www.accenture.com/us-en')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Cognizant',NULL,'Cognizant (Nasdaq: CTSH) is a leading provider of information technology, Agile consulting, and business process outsourcing services. Cognizant‚Äôs single-minded passion is to dedicate our global technology and innovation know-how, our industry expertise and worldwide resources to working together with clients to make their businesses stronger. With over 50 global delivery centers and more than 85,500 employees as of March 31, 2010, we combine a unique global delivery model infused with a distinct culture of customer satisfaction. A member of the NASDAQ-100 Index and S&P 500 Index, Cognizant is a Forbes Global 2000 company and a member of the Fortune 1000 and is ranked among the top information technology companies in BusinessWeek‚Äôs Hot Growth and Top 50 Performers listings. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $16.12B, and a net profit of $2.1B''','http://www.cognizant.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Twitter',NULL,'Twitter is an online social network for real-time self-expression where users can follow other users based on their interests. Users can post real-time status updates, share photos, videos and web links to their followers. Majorly used by celebrities to engage with their fans. Also features live video streaming service. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $3B, and a net profit of $1.2B.''','http://twitter.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Citi',NULL,'Citigroup is a commercial bank provides financial services and products. Their clientele includes consumers, corporations, governments, and institutions. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $97.12B, and a net profit of $18.04B.''','http://online.citi.com/US/login.do')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','KPMG',NULL,'KPMG is a professional services provider offering services like Audit, Tax and Advisory services. It caters to industries like financial services, energy, banking & capital markets, private equity & real estate. Also offers enterprise advisory services for entrepreneurs, family offices & companies.''','http://home.kpmg/xx/en/home.html')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Credit Suisse',NULL,'Credit Suisse is a diversified financial institution providing private banking, investment banking, and wealth management services. Offers M&A advisory, debt and equity financings, divestitures, etc. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $34.1B, and a net profit of $2.1B.''','http://www.credit-suisse.com/us/en.html')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Deutsche Bank',NULL,'Deutsche Bank is a diversified banking and financial services firm. The company offers products & services across retail banking, business and corporate banking, investments among others. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $42.3B, and a net profit of $314M.''','http://www.db.com/company/index.htm')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','AT Kearney',NULL,'ATKearney is a management consulting firm providing consulting services to multiple industries such as retail, energy, chemical, metal and mining, automotive, health and financial services. Solutions offered include cost transformation, merger and acquisition, operations, leadership, analytics and digital transformation.''','http://www.atkearney.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','FINTECH','SEED_ROUND','cardup',NULL,'CardUp is a platform that facilitates users of credit card holders to make big-ticket payments such as house rent, tuition fees, income tax, etc and get rewarded by earning points. The recipients of the funds don''t have to register with the CardUp platform as it uses bank transfers. To offer its service, CardUp needs to develop partnerships with banks and it uses Singapore‚Äôs GIRO network, a way for locals to pay for bills, to facilitate the process. The platform uses Cybersource, a VISA credit card processing company, to take in the information, which has bank-level security and SSL encryption. The platform does not store credit card information and uses tokenization on the backend. CardUp takes a percentage from each transaction which is charged on the persons initiating the transactions. The company was selected as one of 20 finalists participating in the Hackcelerator 2016 at Singapore Fintech Festival. The company is an alumnus of UOB''s FinLab accelerator program 2016. The company is reportedly has raised a pre-seed round of financing.''','http://cardup.co')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','Ernst & Young',NULL,'Ernst and Young provides assurance, advisory, tax and transaction advisory services to business enterprises of all growth level. It has clients in multiple industries such as financial servies, life sciences, real estate, private equity, banking, energy and capital markets.''','http://www.ey.com/en_gl')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','IPO','American Express',NULL,'American Express is a financial institution offering its own branded debit, credit cards, as well as travelers check, and offering issuing services to merchants for payment transactions. Also offers prepaid card solutions under the brand serve. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $43.28B, and a net profit of $6.92B.''','http://www.americanexpress.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','L&T Infotech',NULL,'L&T Infotech is an information technology services and solutions provider. L&T Infotech was founded in June 1997. Its headquarters are located at L&T House, Ballard EstateMumbai. Some of L&T Infotech''s latest acquisitions include Information Systems Resource Centre Pvt. Ltd., Citigroup Fund Services Canada and GDA Technologies, Inc. L&T Infotech has an estimated 15000 employees and an estimated annual revenue of $650M.''','http://www.lntinfotech.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','FMCG','SERIES_A','sugar cosmetics',NULL,'They believe you can make heads turn wherever you go and wear your attitude on your sleeves. They believe in having your back when you‚Äôre short of a back-up plan. We believe you should own your personality, not just wear it. For us, makeup is not just a necessity; it‚Äôs a statement that says, ‚ÄúI am beautiful but a dash of lipstick every once in a while makes me feel sexy‚Äù. They know there is a lot that goes into looking gorgeous which is why they''ve introduced Sugar, a range of cosmetics that complements the sweet & sassy side of you. Their products are everything you need to look stunning while you‚Äôre on the go; you might just fall in love with yourself all over again. That‚Äôs the power of Sugar which lasts long, really long.''','http://sugarcosmetics.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','MEDIA_AND_ENTERTAINMENT','SERIES_A','YourStory',NULL,'YourStory Media is a Bangalore based digital media company that operates a start-up reporting portal called YourStory.com with an aim to promote the entrepreneurial ecosystem in India by publishing original video and text content. It publishes content in multiple vernacular languages including Hindi, Bengali, Marathi, Gujarati, Telegu, Assamese, to name a few. Its flagship product YS Pages is an online database of startups and investors in the country. It operates in other verticals as well namely a job board connects startups and talent a curated manner and a research arm dedicated to market research, intelligence and consulting in the entrepreneurship ecosystem in India. In addition, the company hosts flagship conferences for entrepreneurs including TechSparks, MobiSparks, eSparks, Cloud Conclave, Sociopreneurship, and multiple meetups, boot camps, and workshops.''','http://www.yourstory.com/')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_C','Mindtickle',NULL,'MindTickle offers a SaaS platform for enterprises to train and engage their sales professionals. Companies can share resources such as pitches, presentation decks, and product updates in real time with their employees while also keeping them up to date on the latest product features, objection handling, and customer success stories. The solution also employs social tools and gamification to tap into sales teams'' inner competitiveness and improve usage rates. The platform''s administrative interface enables product and marketing teams to publish new updates, assessments/surveys, and roleplay coaching exercises quickly while providing sales leaders reports and a dashboard that helps them identify knowledge gaps for each representative and the summary views that help track the sales readiness by region, team or user cohort. Won ‚ÄúBest use of engagement techniques in Online Learning‚Äù award at Gamification Summit, SF, the USA in 2013, rated Cool Vendor by Gartner in 2014 and a TiE50 Top Start-Up Winner in 2015. Claims to have their products deployed by 100+ companies with over 1,50,000 users. Clients include SAP, MakeMyTrip, eBay, Yahoo, InMobi, Olacabs, Nutanix, Cloudera.''','http://www.mindtickle.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','MARKETPLACES','SEED_ROUND','playment',NULL,'Playment provides a managed data labeling platform which generates training data sets for computer vision models. Breaks the projects from organizations into small tasks and broadcasts it to a community of skilled workers on the mobile app through a set of APIs. Supports semantic segmentation, cuboidal annotation, line annotation, landmark/polygonal annotation, video annotation, etc. Its QA model consists of worker training, qualification, ranking and response scoring systems. It has use cases in autonomous vehicles, drones, satellite imagery, precision agriculture, retail / eCommerce, sports analytics, banking, and finance industries. Its clientele includes CYNGN, Paytm, Flipkart, Alibaba Group, Agoda, Cotexica, Curalate, etc.''','http://playment.io')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','HEALTHTECH','SEED_ROUND','ray iot (riot) solutions',NULL,'Ray IOT Solutions is the developer of a sleep monitoring device, Ray iCare which assesses respiration patterns and movements of a baby using radar technology. The smart device enables users to assess diseases like Epilepsy, Cardiac Arrests, and Infant Death Syndrome, by monitoring the chest movements of the baby while breathing,. The device also alerts the caretakers in case of a sudden jerk or stopping of the breathing movement.''','http://rayiot.org')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SEED_ROUND','urbanpiper',NULL,'SaaS platform for brands and retailers to acquire, engage and monetize their customers. Provides a cloud hosted service and mobile apps integrated with POS systems to enable flexible loyalty, rewards, messaging and mobile payment solutions for consumers of brands and retailers. HQ in San Francisco, with the technology team based in Bangalore, India. Customers include Chai Point, Ratnadeep Supermarket. Raised an undisclosed amount in seed funding from Axilor and individual investors in Dec 2016.''','http://urbanpiper.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','HEALTHTECH','SEED_ROUND','praktice.ai',NULL,'Praktice is an AI-based virtual assistant for patient engagement & task automation in hospitals. Its virtual assistant Sarah is an AI-backed medical hospital assistant that uses natural language understanding, medical triaging, operational AI, Insurance intelligence, voice and image recognition technologies to navigate care for the patients. It can perform reception repetitive tasks, clinical pathways and provide real-time management insights. Features include customer support personnel, answering patient queries, booking appointments and collecting patient cases. Claims to have trained the assistant in 35 million medical and dental scenarios to understand the patient''s medical context. Clients are Apollo Hospitals, KIMS Global and Singhealth among others.''','http://praktice.ai')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_B','whatfix',NULL,'WhatFix is a SaaS customer engagement startup that helps business on board their customers seamlessly and provides interactive knowledge flows to enhance product adoption. It allows for the creation of interactive support FAQs, training material, and tutorials which can be integrated with ease across all touch-points inside applications. Also provides a community platform for anyone to create, share & execute interactive HowTo guides. The second product of Quicko Labs, earlier having worked on SearchEnabler (SEO platform). Have also filed a patent for their interactive help guides for the web. Part of GSF Accelerator, won DreamPlus Day competition in Seoul in Oct 2014, raising funding from Hanwha Group. Customers include HP, NASA, Booking.com, AAA, Wyndham Worldwide, Flipkart, Instasafe, KartRocket, Greytip Software. Raised $3.7M in a series A round of funding led by Stellaris Venture Partners with participation from existing investors Helion Ventrue Partners and Powerhouse Ventures in April 2017.''','http://whatfix.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_A','freight tiger',NULL,'FreightTiger is an online marketplace for freight logistics, catering to India. Users can connect with carriers based on their requirements and book services. Additionally, the platform also offers features such as freight management, analytics, real-time location visibility, and analytics.''','http://freighttiger.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','EDTECH','SERIES_A','verzeo edutech',NULL,'Verzeo offers online instructor-led courses for college students and recent graduates. The courses offered by the company include ethical hacking, cloud computing, Auto CAD, salesforce management, IoT, finance & marketing, and game development among many others. The training modules include practice problems, case studies, and hands-on resources involving real-life scenarios. In addition to the online courses, the company also allows users to book offline tutoring sessions.''','http://verzeo.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_A','yellow messenger',NULL,'Yellow Messenger is a smartphone app that enables users to discover local businesses for various categories such as restaurants, real estate agencies, automobiles, furniture shops, home service centres etc. Users can also connect with local businesses through instant messaging, contact the restaurant, find the location on a map like interface, post and read reviews posted by others. Also offers a feature to find various offers and deals that are available.''','http://yellowmessenger.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_C','agrostar',NULL,'AgroStar is a product of bio-degradable agrochemicals manufacturer ULink BioEnergy Pvt. Ltd. It provides agri-inputs including fertilizers, seeds, manures, farm equipment, etc. to farmers. The mechanism involves: farmers giving a missed call to the Agrostar center, the executive calling back to the farmer and taking down the order. The order is then home delivered to the farmer. The godown of the company is located in Ahmedabad and claims to have 1 lakh farmers registered with it and INR 5 to 6 crores of goods sold to them till date.''','http://agrostar.in')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Ebay',NULL,'Founded in 1995 in San Jose, CA, eBay connects millions of buyers and sellers globally in the world‚Äôs largest online marketplace, utilizing PayPal to ensure secure transactions. The company also operates specialized marketplaces such as StubHub, the world‚Äôs largest ticket marketplace, and eBay Classifieds sites, which together have a presence in more than 1,000 cities around the world. eBay items can be sold either via a silent auction, in which users input the maximum price they are willing to pay and for which the site will automatically increase bids as necessary up to that maximum, or via ‚ÄúBuy It Now,‚Äù with which they purchase items at a set price. eBay products and companies include eBay Marketplace, Media Marketplace, [PayPal] and various online classifieds. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $10.74B, and a net profit of $2.53B''','http://www.ebay.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','ETMoney',NULL,'ETMoney rebranded from SmartSpends and is a part of Times Internet. Offers a mobile app that allows users to manage their expenses, track their bills, and invest in mutual funds. The company lists funds across various themes. The app automatically tracks all the expenses and transactions done through cards and bank account. As of Sept 2016, ETMoney''s android app had 500K+ downloads.''','http://www.etmoney.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_DPLUS','Freshworks',NULL,'FreshWorks is a cloud-based business management applications provider company. The product portfolio includes Freshdesk (cloud-based customer support software), FreshService (online IT service management software), FreshCaller (cloud-based call center software provider), Freshchat(enterprise chat application), FreshSales (sales CRM software) and Freshmarketer(marketing software for digital marketers), Freshconnect(an enterprise collaboration software), and Freshping(website monitoring tool). Offers subscription-based pricing model. Clientele includes Honda, Toshiba, Cisco, Lenskart, Zoom, Zomato, UNICEF, Team Viewer, Carat Lane, and Money Corp.''','http://www.freshworks.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SEED_ROUND','kruzr',NULL,'Kruzr is a mobile road safety app. It starts automatically every time users start driving and handles all calls and messages, but allows only important communication to reach the user. The app will inform the caller that the user is driving and if it is very important the caller can press 1 (or call again in the free version). All the messages and notifications are hidden until the drive is complete. Has a drive Mode which allows users to access necessary apps seamlessly, while minimizing eyes away from road time. Offers Android app (unreleased) and has 30 installs as of Aug 2016. ''','http://kruzr.co')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','EDTECH','SERIES_A','playshifu',NULL,'Shifu provides Augmented Reality based learning games for kids aged 2-6 years. It is integrated with an app on tablets or smartphones. The app scans for the Shifu cards and launches different learning games such as Safari - to learn about animals, Travel - to learn about transportation, and Jobs- to learn about different occupations.Works with iOS & Android devices''','http://playshifu.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','JP Morgan',NULL,'JPMorgan Chase & Co. is a diversified banking and financial services firm. The company offers products & services across commercial banking and asset management, investments, private banking among others. In 2018, the company recorded revenues of $131.4B and a net profit of $32.5B.''','http://www.jpmorgan.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','NVIDIA',NULL,'Visual computing technology from NVIDIA, inventor of the GPU, which creates interactive graphics on laptops, workstations, mobile devices, notebooks, PCs, and more. The Nvidia GPUs are currently also used by machine learning scientists and data scientists to compute large data faster. Nvidia provides a separate line of products dedicated to Machine Learning and Deep Learning. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $11.71B, and a net profit of $4.14B.''','http://www.nvidia.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','Deloitte',NULL,NULL,'http://www2.deloitte.com/us/en.html')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','FINTECH','UNFUNDED','credit fai‚Çπ',NULL,'Credit Fair is an online purchase financing platform. Offers users loans for purchases up to Rs. 20 lakhs, at 0% interest, payable in EMIs over 2 years. Users can apply for a loan online, get matched with multiple lenders and once approved, users can purchase their desired product. Also provides an auto-debit feature for repayments.''','http://creditfair.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','FINTECH','SEED_ROUND','lendenclub',NULL,'LendenClub is an online marketplace which allows borrowers to get loans from individual lenders. It offers borrowers, personal installment loans starting from INR 25,000 to INR 5,00,000 for a period of 3 months to 24 months. Lenders can invest as low as INR 2000 and earn returns up to 35% (average returns of 25%). Users need to register themselves as lenders or borrowers on the platform by providing their KYC details. The platform conducts a credit check using various sources & proprietary technology. Loans are usually approved within 18 hrs and disbursed within 24 hrs to 30 days. The platform charges borrowers a registration fee of INR 750 and a loan processing fee of 4% of the loan amount or INR 2000 whichever is higher. Lenders are charged a registration fee of INR 500 and a facilitation fee ranging from 1-3% depending on the interest received.''','http://lendenclub.com')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Goldman Sacs',NULL,'Goldman Sachs is a diversified investment solutions firm. Offers a range of services for individuals, institutions, and governments, including investment banking, securities sales & trading, investment management, wealth management, investment research among others. In addition, the company also invests directly through various investment funds across asset classes. Their investing & lending activities include investment in debt securities and loans, public and private equity securities, infrastructure and real estate. Provides investment management & wealth advisory services in equity, fixed income and alternative investments structured as separately managed accounts, mutual funds, private partnerships, and other commingled vehicles. Invests in office, multifamily, hospitality, retail, industrial, self-storage, senior living, healthcare and land across strategies like core-plus, value-add & opportunistic. Makes infrastructure investments in transportation infrastructure (such as airports, ports, railways, and roads), utilities infrastructure (such as electricity, gas and water networks) and energy (such as pipelines, terminals and power generation) in OECD countries with target investment sizes ranging from $100 million to $500 million. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $52.52B, and a net profit of $10.45B''','http://www.goldmansachs.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_C','SigTuple',NULL,'SigTuple provides a data driven, machine-learned, cloud-based solution for detection of anomalies and trends in medical testing to improve the accuracy and efficiency in disease diagnosis. They have a Machine Learning platform called Manthan, which they claim can provide insights from data. They also use deep learning to detect and predict the chances of the person (of whose the images are) having a particular disease from medical diagnostic images. Its peripheral blood smear analyser solution, Shonit, which provides image processing based solution for differential blood count, and screening of diseases like malaria, anaemia, etc., is under clinical trials. As of Feb 2017, it is providing solutions for automated analysis of blood, urine and semen samples, retinal scans and chest x-rays through its continuous learning platform called Manthana. Selected for 4th batch of Google Launchpad accelerator in May 2017.''','http://sigtuple.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Chegg',NULL,'Chegg is an online textbook rental company where students can rent, buy and sell text books from its platform. Can find out textbooks by authors, price and subject categories. Also helps students find colleges, internships and scholarships. Provides homework help to students in various subjects like Math, English, Engineering through real-time online tutoring. Students can choose tutors by universities and high schools. Has a user engagement of over 1M students. Available on iPad/smartphones.''','https://www.chegg.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','McKinsey',NULL,'McKinsey provides global management consulting for firms. It provides solutions for customers to improve the business performance and provides consulting services for users to connect with medical doctors, engineers, designers, data scientists, business managers, civil servants, entrepreneurs, and research scientists. It is available on Apple App Store and Google Play Store.''','http://www.mckinsey.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','UNFUNDED','kawa space',NULL,'Kawa Space designs and operates earth observation satellite constellations for serving multiple business verticals including financial services, government, strategic risk management, and agriculture. The company has won contract for building 27+ satellites for Indian Government and ISRO. In addition, it offers services for building synthetic aperture radar (SAR) and providing hyperspectral imaging solutions.''','http://kawaspace.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','EDTECH','SERIES_A','testbook',NULL,'Testbook.com is offering a web-based platform that enables students to browse through online material and mock tests for MBA (CAT) and M.Tech (GATE) exam preparation. The web portal includes all the engineering streams of under graduation with the feature list that includes mock tests and question banks, preparation timeline for review of the progress, portfolio for tracking performance, ready solutions to all the problems and mock tests available, and analysis regarding the strong and weak areas in their preparation.''','http://testbook.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','TRANSPORTTECH','IPO','Uber',NULL,'Uber offers a mobile application that enables passengers to arrange for a pick-up for travel. Their platform connects passengers and ridesharing services and the mobile app uses phone''s GPS to detect user''s location and connects them with the nearest available ride. Driver''s name and cab details are posted on the mobile app. Pre-ride fare display on the app and credit card billing are offered. Cars are reserved by using the mobile app. Using the app, customers can track their reserved car''s location. The platform also allows a user to register and become a driver in their service. Uber is also experimenting with new services, like its UberRUSH courier service or its UberFAMILY child seat offerings in New York City. Valuation of $62.5B as of June 2016. The company claims to have 40 million monthly active riders as of Oct-2016''','https://www.uber.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','FINTECH','SERIES_DPLUS','tala',NULL,'Tala (formerly InVenture) is a mobile technology company providing simple credit scoring and accounting tools for emerging markets. It uses 10,000+ data points on borrower''s smartphone and builds a credit score which then lenders can refer to while providing loans. Anyone with a smartphone can download the Tala app and apply for short-term credit. Loans are disbursed directly to customers'' mobile wallets in less than a minute. With timely repayment, loan limits increase and interest rates reduce over time. Tala is currently present in East Africa and South East Asia and has originated $300M loans as of Apr''18''','http://tala.co/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_A','hackerearth',NULL,'Web-based developer aggregation and selection platform. HackerEarth offers an online platform for companies to list real-world programming challenges to find the right talent. Recruiters either provide their own coding challenges or choose from the library of questions. Coders participate in coding challenges and HackerEarth provides real-time, automated evaluation of candidate''s aptitude & technical skills. Offers HackerEarth Sprint to automate the entire process of conducting such sprints - starting from creating teams, online collaborative development, tracking progress and peer review/voting to judging the submissions. The tool allows users to connect with various online platforms. Volume based pricing starting at Rs 125 per candidate. The portfolio company of Beenext. Raised $4.5M in a Series A round of funding led by DHI Group in April 2017.''','http://hackerearth.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_A','MX Player',NULL,'MX Player is an online video streaming app for on-demand videos. Allows users to stream VOD content under various categories including movies, TV shows, web series, sports, music videos, live TV channels, etc. in multiple languages. Available for Android and iOS devices. Generates revenue through advertisements and in-app purchases.''','http://www.mxplayer.in')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Mastercard',NULL,'MasterCard is a multinational technology company and financial services corporation. It offers payment systems such as MasterCard credit cards, debit cards, and Maestro and Cirrus ATM cash access cards. It is available in 210 countries and more than 25 thousand banks and financial institutions. It facilitates international transactions while establishing connections between clients and international financial institutions. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $14.95B, and a net profit of $5.85B''','http://www.mastercard.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','PwC',NULL,'PwC provides consulting and auditing services to individuals and organizations. It offers business advisory services, audit and assurance services, tax services, IFRS reporting, family business services, legal services etc. It is network of firms in 157 countries with more than 223,000 people.''','http://pwc.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','BCG',NULL,'Boston Consulting Group (BCG) provides management consulting service to the businesses. Its services include big data & advanced analytics, change management, corporate development and finance, globalization, product development, lean and manufacturing, marketing and sales, M&A and divestitures, and operations. It caters to multiple industries such as automotive, biopharmaceutical, consumer products, education, finance, and retail.''','http://www.bcg.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_B','moveinsync technology',NULL,'MoveInSync is a Bangalore-based employee transportation solutions provider. It offers features including transport routing, employee cab usage record, tracking, automated billing, reporting, and transport security. Aids in route optimization, women security, paperless billing, tracking and delay prediction along with real-time alerts for travellers, reporting dashboard for the organization, etc. Its ETS solution consists of two parts: a touchscreen device installed in the cab and a reliable server hosted in the cloud. The firm claims that its solution is used by over 30,000 employees and 3,500 cabs across nine cities with client companies including Google, Oracle, HSBC, and others. The company charges a licensing fee per transport and also generates revenues by leasing or buying hardware. Incubated in ISB, Hyderabad in 2009.''','http://moveinsync.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','MARKETPLACES','SEED_ROUND','gomechanic',NULL,'Gomechanic is an online closed marketplace for auto garages, providing on-demand car care support. Claims to be providing original spare parts to all partnered garages through centralized procurement. Also offers 3-year guarantees on all spare parts. Provides a dashboard to customers to access car service records, get service reminders, car care tips etc. Claims to have service offerings that are offered at prices 30-50% lower than offline service stations. In Dec 2016, the company raised $250k seed investment from Venture Catalysts.''','http://gomechanic.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','EDTECH','SERIES_C','simplilearn',NULL,'Simplilearn was started as a project management blog in 2009, providing project management tips as well as information on certification and professional training. In 2010, it has started training classes that employed a mixture of classroom and online training. It began offering additional courses across categories, and also offers online training, blended classroom training and exam practice tests in over 200 courses across multiple categories, including IT service management, IT security management, finance management, quality management etc. Has trained about 200K users and conducts 500 unique classes each month as of Jan 2015. Presence in 150+ countries. Acquired Silicon Valley-based Market Motive in a $10M deal.''','http://simplilearn.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','EDTECH','SEED_ROUND','edureka',NULL,'Edureka provides online training courses for Big Data and Hadoop, Hadoop Admin, Cassandra, Data Science, Cloud Computing, Android Development. The courses are provided online with experienced instructors and round the clock online support. Students are assigned projects during the course and are certified upon the completion of the course. The company claims to have raised $250K and counts Jungle Ventures partner Ramakant Sharma as an angel investor. Provides corporate training as well. Clients include Dell, Walmart, Visa, Cisco, Honeywell, etc.''','http://edureka.co')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Foodpanda',NULL,'Foodpanda is an online global takeaway food ordering marketplace. The company claims to have partnered with more than 38k restaurants globally. Enables consumers to choose their meals from nearby restaurants. Helps restaurants generate new business through its online platform. The company also delivers food to customers directly and employs over 10k delivery personnel globally. Provides dashboards along with analytics to vendors.''','https://www.foodpanda.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Boeing',NULL,'Boeing is a manufacturer of commercial jetliners, defense, space and security systems. Its product offerings include the 747, 787, Boeing Business jet range, AH-64 Apache helicopters, CST-100 starliner aircraft and more. The company''s clientele comprises of airlines and governments across 150 countries. The company''s estimated market share in the single-aisle commercial jets is estimated at 43%. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $101.12B, and a net profit of $10.46B.''','http://www.boeing.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','E_COMMERCE','SERIES_C','LivSpace',NULL,'LivSpace is an online retail platform in home decor space. Promoters are founders of one of the top rated design firms in the world (Space Matrix) with a focus on India and South East Asia. Users can browse through room looks, customize it and purchase them. Launched design automation platform to speed up the design and delivery process for its interior designers. The design automation platform provides designers with access to an algorithm-driven library of thousands of editable concepts, edit and combine concepts for creation of mood boards in a few minutes. Also integrates the design concepts with the Livspace e-commerce catalogue of SKUs of products and services. As a result, an automatic, itemized invoice is generated with every concept. Brand was launched in second part of 2013 in India followed by other parts of Asia and Australia. Acquired interior designers marketplace DezignUp and Dwll to expand its community. Also acquired Yofloor a virtual trial room for home furnishings in Sept 2015. Investors include Jungle Ventures, Helion Venture Partners, Bessemer Venture Partners as well as angels including Gokul Rajaram. Has appointed Gopal Dwivedi, former India business head of German furniture maker Hettich, to lead its newly launched modular furniture and wardrobe division.''','http://www.livspace.com/')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Capgemini',NULL,'Capgemini is headquartered in Paris, France and is present in over 40 countries. It is one of the world''s foremost providers of consulting, technology and outsourcing services, enables its clients to transform and perform through technologies. It provides its clients with insights and capabilities that boost their freedom to achieve superior results through a unique way of working, the Collaborative Business Experience. The Group relies on its global delivery model called Rightshore, which aims to get the right balance of the best talent from multiple locations, working as one team to create and deliver the optimum solution for clients. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $15.6B, and a net profit of $861M''','http://www.capgemini.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','FINTECH','SERIES_DPLUS','PhonePe',NULL,'PhonePe provides a UPI-based app for consumers. It enables to send & receive money, pay bills and pay to retail & online merchants. It features solutions for mobile & DTH recharging, paying postpaid & utility bills, checking account balance, online shopping, splitting bills, etc. It helps users to generate the QR code for payment & transactions. The app is available for Android and IOS platforms.''','http://www.phonepe.com/en/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','E_COMMERCE','SERIES_B','shop101',NULL,'Shop101 provides mobile commerce solutions for multi-channel selling. Its features include payment gateways, logistics management, CRM, marketing tools and others. The app allows retailers to sell on WhatsApp, Facebook and Instagram. Its solution enables retailers to create a store on the app, upload products, manage product catalogue and unique link for the mobile store. Its mobile app is available for Android and iOS.''','http://shop101.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','UNFUNDED','black turtle diginovation',NULL,'Black Turtle offers mobile application & web development services. The company''s services include native and hybrid mobile application development, web & desktop application development, enterprise application, UI/UX, digital consulting, e-commerce solution, etc.''','http://blackturtle.io')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','MARKETPLACES','SERIES_C','Magicpin',NULL,'MagicPin is a rewards and cashback platform for diners. Diners can earn cash back if they dine in a partner restaurant of Magic Pin by uploading a photo of the bill along with a selfie with the dish. Thus the app enables discovery through deals/discounts.''','http://magicpin.in/magic/index.php')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','MARKETPLACES','SEED_ROUND','mynewcar',NULL,'MyNewCar is an online car marketplace enabling users to buy new cars at pre-negotiated on-road prices. Buyers can browse & compare available cars, configure a car of their choice, book on-demand test drives, and make a purchase online. The company provides doorstep delivery/pickup of vehicles. Also offers car insurance, financing, and trade-in facilities to its customers. MyNewCar has also launched a P2P test drive booking & car review platform named ''Trivz''.''','http://mynewcar.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','UNFUNDED','devathon',NULL,'Devathon is a premier design and development shop. We help startups bring their product vision to life.''','http://devathon.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','MARKETPLACES','SERIES_B','glowroad',NULL,'GlowRoad is a social product discovery and commerce platform. It provides a mobile app for small businesses to connect with enterprising women in a particular locality, who promote the business'' products and services through online and offline social network and organize an exclusive sale for the business in their locality. Allows the merchant to connect and share product details. Its mobile app is available for Android.''','http://glowroad.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','E_COMMERCE','SERIES_B','slice',NULL,'Slice provides the simplest way to keep track of everything one buys online. By keeping purchase information organized and accessible, Slice is able to present actionable information to consumers when they need it. After signing up, the app automatically pulls information from electronic receipts within email and organizes it in one place for quick, easy reference ‚Äì all while keeping personal information private and secure. With Slice, users can track packages automatically, save money with price drop alerts, access e-receipts and purchase details anytime and track your spending. It even processes electronic receipts from brick & mortar stores that offer e-receipts, such as the Apple store and The Gap. ''','http://slice.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','wadhwani foundation',NULL,'The Foundation‚Äôs primary mission is economic acceleration of emerging economies.''','http://wadhwanifoundation.com')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','UNFUNDED','reckonsys tech labs',NULL,'Responsys (NASDAQ:MKTG) is a marketing cloud software and services company. Their mission is to enable the smartest marketing in the digital world. The most respected brands across the globe use the Responsys Interact Marketing Cloud to manage their digital relationships and deliver the right marketing to their customers across email, mobile, social, display and the web. Their customers gain competitive advantage through the automation, individualization, and coordination of cross-channel marketing interactions at massive scale.Founded in 1998, Responsys is headquartered in San Bruno, California and has offices throughout the world. In 2013, the company was acquired by Oracle.''','http://reckonsys.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_B','silverpush',NULL,'Offers three products namely Unique audio beacon, Pris and Syncads. Unique audio beacon is inaudible beacon which is installed in a TV ads, advertisers can then connect to mobile users listening to these ads (who are identified using an SDK on the phone). Sync ads allows  advertisers to tun personalized TV ads based on live events on various channels and their relativity to the brand. Pris is a TV ad analytics platform which allows advertisers to track impact of ads (maps online activity to TV ad airing) and derive insights from them. Pivoted from mobile retargeting. Accelerated at GSF. Claims to have raised $1.25M in August, 2015.''','http://silverpush.co')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNKNOWN','MuSigma',NULL,'Mu Sigma is a data science and analytics company that helps companies make data-driven decisions. Mu sigma works with organizations across multiple industry verticals solving business problems in horizontals such as Marketing, Risk and Supply Chain. Provides solutions covering data engineering, data science and decision science. Industry verticals include Airline, Hospitality & Entertainment, Pharmaceuticals and Healthcare, BFSI, CPG and Retail. Clients include 140 of the Fortune 500 companies. The company aims to reach $1B in revenues by 2020''','http://www.mu-sigma.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','E_COMMERCE','SERIES_A','shopx',NULL,'ShopX is an online assisted purchase platform catering to rural customers. It provides mobile and web applications for offline retailers to go online and for consumers to access products and services from these retailers. The applications are targeted at cities and towns other than the metros. The company provides an app enabling retailers to offer various products, services, and content to their customers. The company aggregates demand from retailers and allow to sell the products without maintaining a physical stock. The app allows users to browse and purchase products and services from the listed retailers. Also offers a Smart App, for distributors to manage their retail networks.''','http://10i.co.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Adobe',NULL,'Adobe develops multimedia and creativity software products, in addition to rich internet application & software development. Notable products include Photoshop, Portable Document Format (PDF) and Adobe Creative Suite, Adobe Creative Cloud. Product categories include graphics design software, e-learning software, web design programs, web content management software. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $9.03B, and a net profit of $2.59B.''','http://www.adobe.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Tech Mahindra',NULL,'Tech Mahindra is a global systems integrator and business transformation consulting firm focused on the communications industry. Tech Mahindra helps companies innovate and transform by leveraging its unique insights, differentiated services, and flexible partnering models. This has helped customers reduce operating costs, generate new revenue streams and gain competitive advantage. For over two decades, Tech Mahindra has been the chosen transformation partner for wireline, wireless and broadband operators around the world. Tech Mahindra''s ss capabilities span across Business Support Systems (BSS), Operations Support Systems (OSS), Network Design & Engineering, Next Generation Networks, Mobility, Security Consulting, Testing, and other areas. Tech Mahindra√¢‚Ç¨≈∏s solutions portfolio includes Consulting, Application Development & Management, Network Services, Solution Integration, Product Engineering, Managed Services, Remote Infrastructure Management, and BPO. Over 25,000 professionals service clients across the telecom eco-system, from a global network of development centers and sales offices across the Americas, Europe, Middle-east, Africa and Asia-Pacific. With annual revenues in excess of US$ 930 million, Tech Mahindra is the largest telecom-focused solutions provider and 6th largest software exporter from India. Tech Mahindra centers are ISO 9001:2000 certified and it also holds SEI-CMMI Level 5 certification. Tech Mahindra√¢‚Ç¨≈∏s people care practices are certified at PCMM Level 5. The company has also been certified for SSE-CMM Level 3, ISO 20000-1 (IT Service Management Standard) and ISO 27001 (Security Management Standard). In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $5B, and a net profit of $641M''','http://www.techmahindra.com/CWCE.html')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','HP',NULL,'Hewlett-Packard Company (HP) is a global IT company which provides various hardware and software-related solutions to small-medium and large businesses. HP product line includes printers, scanners, digital cameras, calculators, PDAs, servers, computer for personal and workplace. Its enterprise services include HP technology services and enterprise services provisioning Enterprise Security, Storage and networking and other software services. It also holds the portfolio of software-related to business service management, application lifecycle, mobile apps, big data, and analytics. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $58.47B, and a net profit of $5.32B.''','http://www8.hp.com/us/en/home.html')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_A','Aasaan Jobs',NULL,'Building a recruitment system for blue-collared employees for jobs like Data Entry Operator, DTP Operator, Receptionist, Office Staff, Sales/Marketing Staff or Driver. Developing a marketplace with agency backend on the job seekers side to source and benchmark skills as per set standards, and finding employers looking to hire blue collar employees. IIT Bombay founding team. Acquired mHire, blue-collared job portal, in a cash-and-stock deal in June 2017. As of June 2017, the company claims to have 50-500 recruitment vendors active at any point in time (out of a total of 3,000 registered) and about 800 billed clients including India Infoline, HDFC Life, Tata AIA, Uber Technologies Inc. and Ola.''','http://www.aasaanjobs.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Pubmatic',NULL,'Pubmatic offers a sell-side platform for publishers to automate evaluation and sell their ad inventories. Provides unified auction engine with RTB capability across multiple channels, private marketplace, audience data management and ad campaign reporting tools to publishers. Premium publishers can offer all their inventories from a single platform to 400+ Pubmatic demand side partners including DSPs, Adnetworks, Buying desks and Ad exchanges.''','http://pubmatic.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_A','observe.ai',NULL,'Observe provides a conversational intelligence platform which improves the efficiency and performance of the sales team by analyzing the customer conversations. It analyses the customer conversation and gives analysis on key factors such as tone, focus areas, format, and structure.''','http://observe.ai')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Booking',NULL,'Booking.com is a part of Priceline.com (Nasdaq: PCLN),which owns and operates Booking.com. It is a online hotel reservations agency for booking hotel rooms. It attracts over 30 million unique visitors each month via the Internet from both leisure and business markets worldwide. Also provides Bookingsuite with features for website building and hosting, SEO, booking engine, Property management and Reservation systems etc. It was acquired by Priceline in 2007 for $135 Million.''','http://www.rocketmiles.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Phillips',NULL,'Koninklijke Philips N.V. (Royal Philips, commonly known as Philips) is a Dutch technology company headquartered in Amsterdam with primary divisions focused in the areas of electronics, healthcare, and lighting. Philips is organized into three main divisions: Philips Consumer Lifestyle (formerly Philips Consumer Electronics and Philips Domestic Appliances and Personal Care), Philips Healthcare (formerly Philips Medical Systems) and Philips Lighting. Philips has a primary listing on the Euronext Amsterdam stock exchange and is a component of the Euro Stoxx 50 stock market index. It has a secondary listing on the New York Stock Exchange. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $21.4B, and a net profit of $1.3B.''','http://www.usa.philips.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Microsoft',NULL,'Microsoft is an American multinational corporation that develops, manufactures, licenses supports and sells computer software, consumer electronics, and personal computers and services. Its best-known software products are the Microsoft Windows line of operating systems, Microsoft Office office suite, Internet Explorer (IE) web browser and Hyper-V virtualization solution. Also offers Microsoft Dynamics, an ERP solution, for industries of all sizes. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $110.36B, and a net profit of $16.57B''','http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SEED_ROUND','trell',NULL,'Trell is an app-based community driven travelogue sharing platform. It enables users to explore & share travel experiences and travel itineraries with family, friends & others. The app is available on iOS & Google Play''','http://trell.co')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','IPO','Oracle',NULL,'Oracle specializes in developing and marketing database software and technology, cloud engineered systems and enterprise software products. Oracle is the second-largest ERP provider in the world (12% market share). It caters to a range of industries of different sizes. Modules for financials, accounting, project management, procurement, risk management etc are included. Also provides Oracle BPM suite, an iBPMS solution that helps in developing process-centric applications. It supports BAM, social analytics, business rules, real-time optimization. Interactions orchestrated by BPM are stored as instance data that is available to other operational intelligence and big data initiatives. Could be deployed on cloud or on-premise. Its cloud integration platform(iPaaS) has adapters for Oracle E-Business Suite, SAP, Salesforce.com, PeopleSoft, Microsoft CRM, Datacom, CloudScape, Tuxedo. It also provides infrastructure monitoring platform to monitor cloud services and health of entire IT infrastructure - on-premises or in the cloud. It also enables the administrators to be alerted on issues, troubleshoot and resolve them. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $39.83B, and a net profit of $3.82B''','http://www.oracle.com/index.html')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Salesforce',NULL,'Salesforce is an enterprise cloud computing company that provides business software on a subscription basis. The company is best known for its on-demand Customer Relationship Management (CRM) solutions. Offers products catering to sales, service and marketing needs of enterprises through the cloud and mobile app. In addition to CRM tools, analytics and forecasting and collaboration tools are also offered. Chatterbox, one of their major offering provides collaboration services such as sharing knowledge, task management, connects employees with files and data. The company was named the most innovative company by the Forbes Magazine in 2011 and 2012, Fortune magazine places it as the 8th best place to work in the world. App Cloud is a platform by Salesforce for building, running, managing, and optimizing apps. Using the services included in the AppCloud ‚Äì Force, Lightning, Heroku, and Thunder, enterprise and consumer apps can be built and connected to multiple systems. Salesforce has been recognized by Gartner as a leader in the Application Platform as a Service (PaaS) Magic Quadrant. Its major clients are UrbanLadder, InMobi, Y-Axis, and Dunkin Donuts. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $13.28B, and a net profit of $1.11B''','http://www.salesforce.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','MARKETPLACES','SERIES_DPLUS','Meesho',NULL,'Meesho is a social product discovery and commerce platform. It allows users to browse, share and sell products on multiple social media platforms like WhatsApp, Facebook and Instagram. Its platform is an online marketplace which connects resellers and individual sellers with raw material suppliers and end customers. Resellers can create customised catalogues of products using its mobile app which can be shared with buyers. Buyers can also register on its mobile app. Its features include payment gateways, logistics and supply chain management and others.''','http://meesho.com:443/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Redhat',NULL,'Red Hat connects an innovative community of customers, partners, and contributors to deliver an open source stack of trusted, high-performing technologies that solve business problems. Is a billion-dollar 500 company. Provides Linux Platforms, JBoss Middleware, Virtualization, Cloud, Storage and Mobile Solutions spanning over the different industries such as Financial, Government, Health Care, TeleCommunications etc. Some of its customers include Adobe, Intuit, Ca, Avianca, Casio, FICO, and Sprint. Partly operates on a professional open-source business model based on open code, development within a community, professional quality assurance, and subscription-based customer support. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $3.4B, and a net profit of $434M''','http://www.redhat.com/en')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','JioSaavn',NULL,'Saavn is a music streaming platform for on-demand music that allows users to stream and download the songs based on the artists, genres, etc. It offers various features include filtering, toggling between songs, albums, and playlists, metadata searches for artists and music directors etc. It provides "Saavn Social" feature, that allows users to follow friend''s profiles, playlists, and chat as well. It also allows users to follow the specific playlists created by artists and celebrities. The mobile app is available for Android, iOS, and Windows devices. Generates revenue through the freemium model, advertisements, and in-app purchases.''','http://www.saavn.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','SanDisk',NULL,'Sandisk (Acquired by Western Digital in 2015) founded in 1988 by Dr. Eli Harari, an internationally recognized authority on non-volatile memory technology, SanDisk has grown to become the world‚Äôs largest supplier of consumer flash memory data storage products. Serving both consumers and original equipment manufacturers (OEMs), SanDisk designs, develops, manufactures flash storage card products for a wide variety of electronic systems and digital devices. SanDisk currently has more than 860 U.S. patents, more than 550 foreign patents, and more than 1440 patent applications pending in the U.S. SanDisk is the only company, worldwide, that has the rights to both manufacture and sell every major flash card format. With more than 3000 employees and is headquartered in Milpitas, California.''','http://www.sandisk.com/')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','GoDaddy',NULL,'Godaddy, earlier named Jomax Technologies, is an internet domain registrar and web hosting company. Also provides software and services related to e-business. Claims to have over 13 million customers and manages 61 million domains as of February 2016. Recent acquisitions include Marchex and Worldwide Media in April and November 2015.''','http://godaddy.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_DPLUS','BlueJeans Network',NULL,'Provides a cloud-based video conferencing service that enables people to connect with each other any time, any place, and from practically any device. Can support more than 100 simultaneous users on a video conference. Has offices in Mountain View, USA and Bangalore, India. Over 2,000 customer accounts including Facebook, Stanford University, 99 Designs, Wharton University, RedHat, MIT Sloan School of Management.''','http://www.bluejeans.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','IPO','HCL',NULL,'HCL Technologies provides application development, management & maintenance services, cloud computing, CRM, e-commerce, mobility, SAP, systems engineering, IT infrastructure management and other related services. Has a BPO arm - Next Gen BPO with a 400 seater delivery center in the Philippines. It also offers SCM solutions, mechanical engineering services, end to end engineering support and R&D services. Offices in 31 countries. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $8.4B, and a net profit of $1.4B''','http://www.hcltech.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','Bain',NULL,'Bain & Company provides consulting services to the businesses. Provides consulting services in the field of customer strategy & marketing, mergers & acquisitions, performance improvement, and decision making. It caters to multiple industries such as automotive, airlines, financial services, healthcare, oil & gas, and manufacturing.''','http://www.baincapitalventures.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Morgan Stanley',NULL,'Morgan Stanley is a diversified investment solutions firm. Offers a range of services for individuals, institutions, and governments, including investment banking, securities sales & trading, investment management, wealth management, investment research among others. In addition, the company also invests directly through various investment funds across asset classes. Makes real estate investments in global opportunistic and regional core strategies. Their infrastructure investment follows a core-plus & opportunistic strategy focused on the energy & utilities, oil & gas pipelines, transportation, and telecommunications sectors in OECD countries. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $50.19B, and a net profit of $8.74B''','http://www.morganstanley.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','EDTECH','SERIES_DPLUS','Byju''s',NULL,'Byju''s Classes provides coaching for competitive entrance exams like IIT-JEE, CAT, UPSC, GMAT, GRE, Engineering/Medical and supplement courses for grades 6-12. The company is also offering online courses and tablet classes with multi-test and assessment solution, personal feedback and in-depth analysis. The online courses are targeted at K-12 students. Won various awards like CRISIL Emerging India Award and Deloitte Technology Fast 50 Award. Available for Android and iOS platform.''','http://byjus.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Netflix',NULL,'Netflix is an American media-services company that provides subscription-based streaming OTT service which offers online streaming of a library of films and television programs, including those produced in-house. The company operates through three segments namely Domestic streaming, international streaming, and domestic DVD. The domestic streaming segment includes services that stream content to its members in the US. The international streaming segment includes services that stream content to its members outside the US. The domestic DVD segment includes services, such as digital optical disc (DVD)-by-mail. Its in-house developed content is in multiple vernacular languages Spanish, Portuguese, Korean, Polish, Turkish, Hindi, among others. As of October 2018, the company has 137 million total subscribers worldwide, including 58.46 million in the United States. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $15.79B, and a net profit of $1.21B.''','http://www.netflix.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_DPLUS','Gainsight',NULL,'Previously known as Jbara, Gainsight, a customer success management solution helps subscription-based businesses to drive their customer success initiatives, proactively manage retention, reduce churn and grow revenue by uncovering up-sell opportunities. Leverages big data analytics across sales data, usage logs, support ticket, surveys and other sources of customer intelligence. Key Customers include Adobe, BazaarVoice, Marketo, Influtive and Gild.''','http://www.gainsight.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Nearbuy',NULL,'Nearbuy, rebranded from Groupon India, part of US based public-listed company Groupon Inc., is an online local coupon and deals generating platform. Aggregates group buying deals from various offline merchants like restaurants, spas, leisure & activity providers and also some eCommerce stores. The firm also provides merchants with a collection of products and services, including customizable deal campaigns, credit card payment processing capabilities and point-of-sale solutions. It was formed in early 2011 after Groupon Inc. bought the Indian deal-of-the-day website SoSasta and and re-branded it as "Crazeal by Groupon Inc". After winning a battle to acquire the groupon.co.in domain name, the Indian business was renamed Groupon India in Nov 2012. The company has raised ‚Äòexternal funding‚Äô of $20 million led by Sequoia Capital in March 2015. The company has restructured post-rebranding to NearBuy and Groupon does not control majority stake in the business. As of Sep 2016, the company is present in 33 cities with a merchant base in excess of 50,000 while claiming to generate a footfall of over 500,000 per month for its offline merchants. As of Nov 2016, claims that 60% of the business comes through the app.''','http://www.nearbuysystems.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Booz Allen Hamilton',NULL,'Booz Allen Hamilton provides products & services covering management consulting, analytics, and engineering for cybersecurity and digital IT to the organizations. Products include District Defend, a mobile, location-based security solution for BYOD devices to enforce organizational policies and secure proprietary and sensitive information; Appcritique, a mobility security tool for commercial and custom apps; Cybersmart, a cybersecurity management tool to automate & track workflows; Oceanlens, a 3D, geographic data visualization tool for training, mission planning, & operations; Sailfish, a big data analytics platform; Polaris, a project analysis solution; and Bento, an objective assessment toolkit. Services include Cyber4Sight, a managed security monitoring and intelligence reporting for contextual & actionable cyber threat data; Cyberm, a cybersecurity maturity model consulting; Insider4Sight, an insider threat detection by evaluating data access and anomalies; and ID Protection & Exploitation, a biometric-based identity protection solution. Awarded as the Top 2014 Workplace by the Washington Post in 2014. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $6.17B, and a net profit of $0.3B''','http://www.boozallen.com')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','Akamai Technologies',NULL,'Akamai Technologies offers a platform providing edge delivery solutions. Provides a platform known as Akamai Intelligent Edge Platform that delivers edge security, web and mobile performance, enterprise access, and video delivery solutions to sites, users, devices, data centers & clouds. Partners include IBM, Philips, Adobe, Honda and more.''','http://www.akamaitechnologies-track-day.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','CapitalOne',NULL,'Capital One is a commercial bank. It offers personal, commercial and business banking services for consumers, small businesses and commercial clients. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $32.37B, and a net profit of $6.01B.''','http://www.capitalone.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'IPO','HSBC',NULL,'HSBC is a commercial bank. They provide commercial banking, global banking, global private banking, retail banking and wealth management. It serves in 67 countries across the world. In 2017, the bank recorded revenues of $64.3B and a net income of $13.7B.''','http://www.hsbc.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'SERIES_B','Rakuten',NULL,'Rakuen is an online marketplace for multi-category products, the largest of its kind in Japan. The company started out as MDM in 1997 before changing to its current name in 1999. Product categories include apparels, electronic gadgets, mobile phones, footwear, home decor, and more. The company became public in April, 2000 through an IPO on the JASDAQ market.''','http://global.rakuten.com/corp')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','MEDIA_AND_ENTERTAINMENT','IPO','Facebook',NULL,'Facebook is an online social networking platform where users can connect friends & other users around the globe. Users can create their personal profile, create group & pages, add friends, exchange messages, post status updates and photos, share videos and receive notifications when others update their profiles. Users can join common-interest user''s groups organized by workplace, school or college, or other characteristics, and categorize their friends into lists. Also features social games where users can get engage with their friends. The app is available for both iOS and Android users. Monetizes through advertisements and promotional content. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $55.83B, and a net profit of $22.11B''','http://www.facebook.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','OnePlus',NULL,'OnePlus is an internet first brand of mobile phones and accessories. Product catalog includes mobile phones, headsets, phone cases, and power cables. The company sells products through retailers such as Amazon, Flipkart, Paytm and others. The company has also opened offline stores.''','http://oneplus.net')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','FINTECH','MnA','Paypal India',NULL,'PayPal is an online payment and money transfer service that allows people to send money via email, phone, text message or Skype. They offer products to both individuals and businesses alike, including online vendors, auction sites and corporate users. PayPal Mobile is one of PayPal‚Äôs newest products. It processes over 12.5 million payments with 165 million active consumer accounts in over 203 countries. In 2015, PayPal was spun off as an independent company from eBay, which had previously wholly-owned it since 2002 as a subsidiary. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $15.45B, and a net profit of $2.05B.''','http://www.paypal.com/us/home')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SEED_ROUND','plivo',NULL,'Plivo provides a cloud-based API platform that enables developers and businesses to build Voice and SMS apps without carrier lock-in for their web and mobile apps in the cloud. The APIs aid to make and receive calls, send SMS, make a conference call etc. Developers can create Session Initiation Protocol (SIP) endpoints to perform the telephony operations. Plivo runs on its own servers in order to have more control over the quality of service. The company is a 2012 Y Combinator graduate.''','http://www.plivo.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','FINTECH','SERIES_DPLUS','BankBazaar.com',NULL,'Bankbazaar is an online financial products distribution & comparison platform. Enables users to buy personal loan, home loan, auto loan, and education loan products; debit & credit cards; life insurance, health insurance, auto insurance, home insurance and travel insurance products; and mutual funds, fixed deposits and savings accounts. Users need to provide their basic details to apply for a product online and can track its status.''','http://www.bankbazaar.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774',NULL,'UNFUNDED','Bosch',NULL,'Bosch is a manufacturer & supplier of automotive powertrain, chassis control & electronic components to OEMs and tier 1 companies. Manufactures diesel & gasoline engine, car brake systems, fuel-injection equipment, brake systems, electronic component systems, transmission parts, driver assistance systems, sensors and semiconductor products for four wheeler, two wheeler, ship, and rail transportation. Bosch also manufactures components for BPO, drive and control technology, energy and building solutions, large thermal plants and system solutions, packaging technology, power tools for professionals, security solutions and software solutions''','http://www.bosch.com')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','E_COMMERCE','SERIES_DPLUS','Droom Technology',NULL,'Droom is an online marketplace to buy and sell used automobiles. Provides verified listings for buyers along with tools to view, schedule, negotiate and communicate with the seller. Sellers can manage their listings, and have tools for price estimates, rating management, and dispute resolution. Also, has a feature called ''Droom Assist'' which provides personalized support to users for choosing which car to buy. Tied up with JetSetGo to sell and lease aircrafts and helicopters. As of April 2016, has 47,000 B2C sellers, 23,600 products, and 57,000 listings on its platform while claiming 3,500 transactions in the month of April. The company is doing $160 million in annualized run rate of gross merchandise value (GMV or cost of goods sold) and targets to grow to $500 million by March 2017. It is present in 142 cities with plans to launch overseas by October 2016. Has close to 750K visitors coming every month with over 300K app downloads across Android and iOS platform. Founding team from Microsoft, Apple, Yahoo backgrounds. Raised $16M from LightBox Ventures and Japanese firm Beenos. Ties up with Uber to bring chopper rides to Indian customers as of Dec 2015. Launched auto inspection app ECO in association with Carnation in April 2016. Raised nearly $30M Series B funding round led by Beenext Digital Garage with participation from Lightbox Ventures, Beenos and new undisclosed Japanese and Chinese institutional investors. Partnered with lending platform Cashcare in Sep 2016. Raised $20M in Series C round of funding led by Integrated Asset Management & Digital Garage along with participation of existing investors in Jul''17''','http://www.droom.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','FINTECH','SEED_ROUND','indwealth.in',NULL,'INDWealth is a wealth management platform based on machine learning, AI and data science technology. Features include goal-based financial planning & future projections; portfolio management; tax analytics & tax-saving strategies and personalized recommendations of investment products.''','http://indwealthin.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','2020-04-13 00:59:02.774','ENTERPRISETECH','SEED_ROUND','spotdraft',NULL,'Spotdraft is an online cloud-based AI-enabled contract-creator and invoice sending platform. It allows businesses and freelancers to create contracts through their website, by just entering a few details and selecting the type of contract. Users can also send customized invoices to their clients, and accept payments from them. Claims that the AI-enabled platform has the capability to provide feedback on existing contracts. As of Nov 2017, claims to have 4000+ contracts processed with Beta stage platform.''','http://spotdraft.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','ENTERPRISETECH','UNFUNDED','ipsator analytics',NULL,'Ipsator is a cloud based customer feedback management tool making use of tablets. Provides for tablets used for collecting feedback from customers. Also provides insights and suggestions for improvement in business processes based on customer feedback. Currently in beta mode and patent is still pending. ''','http://ipsator.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','FINTECH','SERIES_DPLUS','PolicyBazaar',NULL,'Policybazaar is an online insurance aggregator for comparative analysis of products from various insurers based on price, quality and key benefits. Currently, the website offers information to users to help them make informed decisions along with solution driven customer service. They feature content in various forms such as top five features of a product, best sellers and conversion rates. Raised $40M in April 2015 for Series D round from PremjiInvest.''','http://policybazaar.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','CLEANTECH','SEED_ROUND','zunroof',NULL,'ZunRoof offers free energy audit services for the existing grid-connected system. The company designs a customized solar system for every client and offers the complete solar solution with the option of net-metering PV System and battery-backed hybrid system. ZunRoof also offers free post-installation services. The company caters to homeowners, institutions, real estate & corporate players. Offers solar home tech apps and IoT based remote monitoring systems.
''','http://zunroof.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','FMCG','SERIES_DPLUS','licious',NULL,'Licious is a path breaking concept in the Indian Food industry; aimed at solving the perennially existing problem of finding safe, delectable, trustworthy fresh meat in India.The company builds a world-class enterprise that''s bound to upgrade the way the company procures, sells, buys, and consumes meat in India.''','http://licious.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'SERIES_B','Digit Insurance',NULL,'Digit is an IRDA licensed internet first general insurer launched by Fairfax Holdings and Kamesh Goyal, a former executive from Allianz. Fairfax holds 45% stake in the company. Offers insurance for cars, mobile handsets, travel, and jewellery.''','http://www.godigit.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','EDTECH','UNFUNDED','dare2compete.com',NULL,'Dare2Compete is an online platform to discover competitions and academic events like B-School competitions, business quizzes, debates, conferences. Students can also participate in online live quizzes. Colleges can list and promote their competitions and campaigns on the platform.''','http://dare2competecom.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Sprinklr',NULL,'Sprinklr provides a full suite of social media management tools to post across social networks and measure engagement for enterprise. Enables brands to publish, advertise, and analyse their marketing campaigns with features like monitoring social media conversations and responding to clients. Allows users to manage paid campaigns, content lifecycle and build websites with easy to use drag and drop features. Partners include Accenture, Cognizant, Deloitte, IBM, RichRelevance, SHIFT and ThisMoment. Acquired newBrandAnalytics, Scup, Branderati, Dachis Group, TBG, GetSatisfaction and Pluck.''','http://www.sprinklr.com')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','MARKETPLACES','SERIES_A','docsapp',NULL,'Smartphone app enabling patients to consult with health specialists for health queries through a WhatsApp chat-like interface. Claims of having partnered with reputed MD doctors from Bangalore, Mumbai, and Delhi with 2000 doctors on board. Offers both Android and iOS apps. Claims to have 80K + registered users with 15K+ using the service at least once a month.''','http://docsapp.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'SERIES_B','olx',NULL,'OLX is an online classifieds platform that enables its users to create ads and displays them on social networks.The platform enables its users to design ads with pictures and videos; control their selling, buying, and community activities in My OLX; display their ads on social networking profiles; access the site from their mobile phones, and view OLX accounts in their local languages.The company offers its services in the United States and internationally. As of August 4, 2010, OLX operates as a subsidiary of Myriad International Holdings B.V.''','http://www.olx.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','ENTERPRISETECH','SEED_ROUND','freightwalla',NULL,'Freightwalla is an upcoming company, claims to be a mix of analytics, automation and logistics technology. Provides an online platform for booking cross-border freight, aimed at small to medium size enterprises.''','http://freightwalla.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','ENTERPRISETECH','UNFUNDED','accubits technologies',NULL,'Accubits is a global software and IT services company focusing on Artificial Intelligence, Blockchain, Virtual and Augmented Reality, and Enterprise solutions. In the Blockchain domain it offers services such as dAppp development, token development, smart contract deployment etc. Develops its platforms on Ethereum, Hyperledger primarily.''','http://accubits.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','FINTECH','SERIES_C','rupeek',NULL,'Rupeek is an internet enabled lending platform connecting lenders and borrowers for gold loans. Registered borrowers specify their loan requirements. The authenticity of the gold is verified by an agent and a credit risk model is implemented and the money is transferred to the borrower. It claims to offer low interest rates and paper work. ''','http://www.rupeek.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','ENTERPRISETECH','SERIES_A','dropthought',NULL,'DropThought‚Äôs Feedback Platform empowers companies, brands, and marketers to engage with their customers and employees in real-time to gather, respond, and analyze feedback that leads to improved experiences and improved NPS. Instant feedback can be gathered in three ways: via its mobile app, embedded API integrations, and on-site using tablet devices. It‚Äôs analytics dashboard and manager mobile app can notify managers and brands to feedback reported in the moment, to enable immediate responses, insights, and resolution. It‚Äôs text analytics solution allows businesses to see customer experience metrics over time and quickly identify opportunities to improve. Companies can also easily select and promote customers positive instant feedback on social channels. Some of its customers include Cisco, Adobe, Juniper, NTT''','http://dropthought.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','MEDIA_AND_ENTERTAINMENT','SERIES_DPLUS','BookMyShow',NULL,'BookMyShow is an online ticketing portal for movies and events. It was launched in 2007 by the parent company Big Tree Entertainment (estd. 1999). Along with movie/play tickets, the company is an exclusive ticketing partner of several sporting franchises in India including Formula 1, Indian Premier League, Aircel Chennai Open etc. The company has also expanded to global markets like Malaysia and New Zealand. Has a market share of 85 to 90 percent in the online entertainment-ticketing market. As of March 2015, 70 percent of its sales comes from movie tickets and the remaining from sports, plays and live events. Its main sources of revenue (85%) comes from the convenience fee charged on each ticket; the sale of ticketing software, including maintenance fees, to multiplex theatres brings in 5%, and turnkey solutions for events and sports such as IPL contributes to around 10% of revenue as of Sept. 2014. Acquired Ticketgreen, a South India focussed ticketing portal in March 2013. Acquired a majority stake in Bangalore-based social media analytics startup Eventifier for over $1 million (Rs 6.2 crore). Acquired Chennai-based fan relationship management and analytics startup Fantain Sports as part of a move to expand reach and grow user base. Raised INR 550 Cr in July 2016, at a valuation of INR 3000 Cr, led by Stripes Group (first investment in India) and existing investors Accel, SAIF and Network18. Claims to have seen about 100M transactions on its platform in 2015-16. Has presence in Bangladesh, New Zealand, Indonesia, UAE and launched operations in Sri Lanka in Oct 2016. In Feb 2017, the company acquired a 75% stake in Townscript''','http://in.bookmyshow.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'IPO','Nomura',NULL,'Nomura is a retail bank. It offers retail banking, merchant banking, asset management, wholesale(global markets and investment banking) and other services to individuals, institutions, corporates and governments. It has operations in more than 30 countries across the world. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $16.7B, and a net loss of $-712M.''','http://www.nomura.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'IPO','Nielsen',NULL,'Nielsen is a global information and measurement company that enables companies to understand consumers and consumer behavior by measuring and monitoring what consumers watch and the brand''s consumers associate with on a global and local basis. Delivers critical media and marketing information, analytics and manufacturer and retailer expertise about what and where consumers buy and what consumers read, watch and listen to on a local and global basis. It also provides a constant, real-time stream of information, revealing tuning behavior during programs and commercials. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $6.5B, and a net loss of $-712M.''','http://www.nielsen.com/us/en/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'SERIES_A','Little Black Book',NULL,'Little Black Book/LBB is a web and mobile app based discovery and recommendations platform for local places, services, and events. Launched by Suchita Salwan & Dhruv Mathur, LBB generates community-led recommendations across categories, providing unique local discoveries through feeds and map-based interfaces. Uses community-driven recommendations as a medium to drive an engaged audience of millennials to local enterprises, places, and experiences with over 30k recommendations across over 18 categories. Allows users to follow others, create a custom feed based on their interests and post their experiences on the platform. Users can also save the content and share on social media like Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram. Claims that it gets 7M+ page views every month from more than 2M users with around 85% traffic from mobile platforms. Has more than 200k app downloads on Google Play store & App store with around 4.6-star rating. Claims that the platform has grown over 300% with respect to user-reach, over 500% with respect to revenue growth, and from 1 to 8 cities including Delhi, Bangalore, Mumbai, Kolkata, Pune, Goa, Gurgaon, and Chennai in 12 months, as of Oct''17. LBB has recently raised INR 65M from Blume Ventures, and its existing partners, IDG Ventures and Indian Angel Network (IAN). With this investment, the total capital raised by LBB stands at INR 156M. Also, angels investors such as Rajan Anandan of Google India, Sachin Bhatia of TrulyMadly & MakeMyTrip.com have also invested in the company.''','http://lbb.in:443/')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'IPO','Vodafone',NULL,'Vodafone Group plc is a British Multinational Telecommunications company head-quartered in London operating in 26 countries and has partners in over 50 additional countries providing Mobile and fixed communication services.Its Vodafone Global Enterprise division provides telecommunications and IT services to corporate clients in 150 countries.Vodafone has a primary listing on the London Stock Exchange and is a constituent of the FTSE 100 Index. As of Feb 2016, Vittorio Collao is the CEO of Vodafone Group. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $53.9B, and a net loss of $-3.8B''','http://vodafone.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','FINTECH','IPO','ICICI Bank',NULL,'ICICI Bank is India''s largest private sector bank with total assets of INR 7,206.95B ($109B) as of March 2016. The bank has a network of 4,850 Branches and 13,660 ATMs across India. It offers a wide range of banking products and financial services to corporate and retail customers through a variety of delivery channels and through its specialized subsidiaries in the areas of investment banking, life and non-life insurance, venture capital, and asset management. The Bank currently has subsidiaries in the United Kingdom, Russia and Canada, branches in United States, Singapore, Bahrain, Hong Kong, Sri Lanka, Qatar, and Dubai International Finance Centre and representative offices in United Arab Emirates, China, South Africa, Bangladesh, Thailand, Malaysia, and Indonesia. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $18.7B, and a net profit of $617M''','http://www.icicibank.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'IPO','Axis Bank',NULL,'Axis Bank offers a wide range of financial services to Large and Mid-Corporates, MSME, Agriculture and Retail Business. It has more than 2,500 branches and 12,500 ATMs. The overseas operations of the Bank are spread over its 7 international offices with branches at Singapore, Hong Kong, DIFC (Dubai International Financial Center), Colombo, Shanghai and respective offices at Dubai and Abu Dhabi. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $9.1B, and a net profit of $71M.''','http://www.axisbank.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','TRANSPORTTECH','SERIES_C','ZoomCar',NULL,'Zoomcar is an online rental platform for self-drive cars. It allows individuals to rent vehicles by the hour, day, week or month. The service is based on a hyper-local distribution model that locates vehicles in close proximity to where people live or work. Rental cars are delivered to the doorstep or can be picked up from designated pick up points. The company refunds users for fuel consumption. It also offers cars with All India permits. The company also provides cycles for rent. The company has also forayed into subscription-based model for cars through its ZAP service. Its mobile app which is available for Android and iOS.''','http://www.zoomcar.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Flipkart',NULL,'Online shopping portal with a wide catalogue and variety of products. Operates its own payment gateway, Payzippy (shut down in Aug 2014) and logistics service provider, eKart Logistics. Bought 34% stake in MapmyIndia, digital mapping firm, to boost its supply chain. In Dec 2016, Flipkart sold a small stake worth INR 260 crores to BCCL for cash and advertising space in the latter''s media properties. Raised $1.4 billion (at $11.6B valuation) in April 2017 from Tencent, eBay, and Microsoft and has reached an agreement to acquire eBay India. As of Nov''17, planning to enter into online grocery services and has launched a pilot programme in Bangalore with availability to selected customers. As of Aug''17, planning to sell refurbished electronic gadgets also. Raised $1.5B from Softbank in Aug''17. Launched private label fashion apparel brand Metronaut under men''s fashion category in Jul''17. As of Oct''17, launched private label home appliances like TV and Microwaves under its brand Marq and planning to expand to categories like washing machines and ACs. Launched its own branded smartphone Caputre+ in partnership with Smartron in Nov''17. Walmart acquired 77% stake in May, 2018.''','http://www.flipkart.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'UNKNOWN','Dunzo',NULL,'Dunzo is a mobile-based concierge services provider operating in India. Its app is available on iOS and Android. Users can avail errand services and tasks across various categories such as buying, shipping, home repairs, home services and more through the company''s platform. The company uses its own fleet of errand runners or coordinates with local merchants/vendors to deliver the task. Users can pay for the service either directly to the service provider or through the in-app feature. The mobile app is available for download from the App Store and Play Store.''','https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/dunzo/id701772884')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'IPO','Blackrock',NULL,'BlackRock is an investment firm. Provides asset management services to individuals, governments, companies & foundations. Offers equity, fixed income & multi-asset strategy investments through exchange-traded funds and active strategies through mutual funds and separately managed accounts. Makes equity & debt infrastructure investments in renewable energy, transport, energy, power, and social infrastructure. Private real estate investments include core & opportunistic direct investments and debt investments in offices, apartments, retail centers, and hotels across the US, Europe & Asia Pacific. Makes public real estate investments in REITs and CMBS. Also invests in commodity funds and emerging market equity funds. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $14.19B, and a net profit of $4.3B''','http://www.blackrock.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','ENTERPRISETECH','UNFUNDED','flobiz',NULL,'Flobiz provides business management software for SMBs. Various features offered by the product are sales report management, GST invoice generation, expense tracking, customer management, payment management, supplier management, and more. This can also be integrated with tally software.''','http://flobiz.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','MEDIA_AND_ENTERTAINMENT','SERIES_DPLUS','Hike',NULL,'Hike Messenger is a P2P messaging and Voice over IP (VoIP) application that combines chat, messaging, feeds, and integrations with third-party transportation and payment applications. The application allows creating group chats for up to 1,000 members for sharing large videos, original uncompressed images, documents of any type (DOC, .MP3, .ZIP to name a few). It features an array of over 15,000 stickers that users can send each other, images ranging from Indian festival greetings to Bollywood stars and Game of Thrones characters. Users are allowed to send each other over 300 million stickers a day, in addition to the 40 billion text messages on the platform. Some of the supported languages include English, German, French, Portuguese, Russian, Spanish, to name a few. The application registered a user base of over 100 million in 2017.''','http://www.hike.in/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','TRAVELTECH','SERIES_B','stanza living',NULL,'Stanza Living is a managed accommodation provider for students. It offers fully furnished hostels for students on a monthly rental basis. Offers single and twin-sharing accommodations. Students can search for space of their choice by applying the location filter and schedule visits via the platform. Some of the amenities provided are food, fully furnished rooms, security, housekeeping, play areas, community-driven resources, and more. The company also offers biometric and CCTV-based security services in its facilities. Its mobile app is available for both Android and iOS devices.''','http://stanzaliving.com')
;
INSERT INTO public.companies (created_at,updated_at,category,funding_stage,"name",num_employees,vision_statement,website) VALUES 
('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','ENTERPRISETECH','SEED_ROUND','hevo data',NULL,'Hevo is a data integration platform. Helps in moving data from one source to another. Connects to the source and using the transformation code transfers data to the warehouse. Features include automatic detection and handling of the schema change, real-time alerts & notifications on data pipeline, zero data loss, joining tables and writing queries.As of Nov 2017, claims to have integration for 100+ data sources. Monthly pricing plans based on the number of data sources and events.''','http://hevodata.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','ENTERPRISETECH','UNFUNDED','competent groove',NULL,'Competent Groove is a SaaS-based field force automation and sales force automation solutions provider. Its product offerings include FeetPort which is a field service management software. Its features include location analytics, mobile POS, real-time updates, auto task management, customer order management, and capturing geotagged media. It offers a subscription-based pricing model. ICICI Bank, Vodafone, Jaquar, and NecLife are part of its clientele.''','http://competentgroove.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','ENTERPRISETECH','SEED_ROUND','mate labs',NULL,'Mateverse is a machine learning-based search engine. It incorporates user‚Äôs context and emotions for results. It has a chatbot to facilitate the search and also offers machine learning training to businesses. As of October 2016, the product is yet to be launched.''','http://matelabs.in')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','FINTECH','SEED_ROUND','One Score',NULL,'FPL believes that consumption credit presents a very large opportunity in India and the credit card is the best product to offer consumption credit to India‚Äôs growing younger population. Card acceptance has trebled in the three years after demonetisation and every category is getting digitized. Like the overall growth in adoption of digital payments, the adoption of credit cards too has grown, both in terms of card issuance and spends. However, the experience of using a credit card has not evolved to serve the digitally savvy young millennials. FPL has created a proprietary full-stack technology platform to deliver a nex-gen credit card experience to its customers. Customers can use an intuitive mobile app along with their credit cards to manage every aspect of their credit life cycle. FPL launched the OneScore app in July this year to help customers understand and manage their credit score and behavior in a simple and secure way.''','https://www.onescore.app/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'IPO','IBM',NULL,'IBM, an acronym for International Business Machines, is a multinational computer technology and consulting corporation. IBM''s Watson is a completely dedicated Cognitive Platform which can understand natural language and extract insights from unstructured texts. They provide APIs and SDKs for developers. IBM acquired Lombardi BPM in 2009. It supports integrated analysis, simulation, and testing. Unique ''Process Coach'' UIs guide users through complex runtime tasks. It enables developers to mix and match IBM products with software from other companies. and spliced it with its existing BPM. As of today more than 350 companies and startups are using Watson platform. IBM''s Master Data Management (MDM) solutions provide a simple and trusted view of data. IBM infosphere manages multiple domains of master data and reference data. According to Gartner, IBM''s total software revenue from MDM of customer data solutions in 2014 was $114.3 million. It also provides products like urban code for automated cloud deployment. It is home to 5 Nobel Laureates, 9 US National Medals of Technology, 5 US National Medals of Science, 6 Turing Awards, 10 Inductees in US Inventors Hall of Fame and counting. Also provides IBM Cast Iron, a cloud-based integration platform to integrate with Salesforce, SAP, Oracle ERP, etc. IBM provides a Big Data Platform for Analytics. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $79.59B, and a net profit of $8.72B''','http://www.ibm.com/us-en/?ar=1')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','EDTECH','SERIES_B','Vedantu',NULL,'Vedantu is an online tutoring platform for school students of class 6 upwards. Offers live tutoring with two-way interaction via whiteboard, audio and video, which works on a low bandwidth. Provides certified tutors from IIT Bombay, IIT Roorkee, BITS Pilani, etc. Monthly and flexible hour based pricing plans. Pivoted from developer of white label mobile learning applications in April 2014 and launched online tutoring platform public in October 2014. Went from 80 registered users in October 2014 to 2500 registered users by year end. 3000+ registered users and 1300+ hours of live learning as of Jan 2015. ''','http://vedantu.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','E_COMMERCE','SERIES_C','CarDekho',NULL,'CarDekho, owned by Girnar Automobile Pvt. Ltd., is an online platform which offers a database of cars in categories, ranging from new launches to upcoming models, from brand names to body types, from price ranges to popular choices, etc. The company also provides a platform for users to list their pre-owned cars to sell. Buyers can search for cars based on their location, price, brand, and more. It provides its visitors with car reviews, and e-commerce services to help them reach out to the automobile dealers. Provides Cardekho ‚ÄúTrustmark‚Äù as a stamp of verification for cars that the company has inspected to build customer''s trust. Offers automobile finance for those who want to buy a car on loan working in collaboration with BankBazaar.com. Has started tyredekho.com to list details of various tires used for automobiles. Acquired BuyingIQ for an undisclosed amount in April 2015, to capitalize on their data analytics capabilities which analyses millions of curated product reviews crawled from all over the internet. Launched automobile battery research and discovery platform BatteryDekho. CarDekho has also launched its own digital loan platform through tie-ups with HDFC Bank, Axis Bank, Tata Capital, and Mahindra Finance''','http://www.cardekho.com/')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Myntra',NULL,'Myntra is an online marketplace for multi-category fashion products. Its catalog includes apparel, footwear, accessories, etc catering to men, women, and kids. The company has expanded to sell electronics, beauty, and home decor items. It also sells its own brand of fashion products.''','http://www.myntra.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','VMWare',NULL,'VMware provides virtualization solutions. The company was founded in 1998 and is headquartered in Palo Alto, California. Its virtualization platform products include ''Player'' that enables individuals to run virtual machines on their desktops; Fusion, a desktop virtualization product for users of Intel-based Apple Macintosh computers; Workstation for software developers and enterprise IT professionals; Server, which enables virtual partitioning of a server; ESX Server, an enterprise-class virtualization platform that runs directly on the hardware; Virtual SMP that enables a virtual machine to use four physical processors simultaneously; and VMFS, which allows multiple ESX Servers to share block-based storage. The company also offers VirtualCenter that provides a central point of control to manage a virtualized IT environment; VMotion, which allows users to move virtual machines; DRS that creates resource pools from physical servers; HA which provides automated recovery from hardware failure; Consolidated Backup that enables LAN-free automated backup of virtual machines. Virtual Desktop Manager, a desktop management server that connects users to their virtual desktops. VMware vRealize Automation automates the delivery of personalized infrastructure, applications and custom IT services. Automates end-to-end delivery and management of infrastructure and accelerating application deployment and releases. The company also provides products for security, and their offering includes a product for network security, cloud security, and application security. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $9B, and a net profit of $2.4B.''','http://www.vmware.com')
,('2020-04-13 00:59:02.775','2020-04-13 00:59:02.775',NULL,'SERIES_DPLUS','Cisco',NULL,'Cisco is a manufacturer of networking equipment. Its portfolio of products includes optical networking, storage area networking equipment, Management interfaces and software interfaces for network functionality. It also provides solutions for security across network and applications. Their offerings for security includes products for cloud security, endpoint security, email security, multi-factor authentication solution, and a firewall. In 2018, the company recorded annual revenues of $49.33B, and a net profit of $0.11B''','http://www.cisco.com')
;


